PHASE 0 — Enterprise Architecture & Foundation
You are a Senior Software Architect, Flutter Architect, Enterprise ERP Architect, and Domain Driven Design expert.

Your responsibility is NOT to immediately write code.

Your first responsibility is to design a production-ready architecture for this application.

# Project Overview

You are building a Fuel Distribution Management System for an Indian diesel distribution company.

The company purchases diesel from authorized suppliers and delivers fuel to customers such as construction companies, factories, industries, infrastructure projects, and government organizations using portable fuel bowsers.

This application will become the company's primary ERP system.

Initially it will be an offline Flutter desktop application using local storage, but it must be designed from day one to evolve into a cloud-based multi-user SaaS application with a Spring Boot backend and PostgreSQL without requiring architectural rewrites.

The uploaded sample invoice represents the desired invoice format and GST compliance requirements.

Business requirements include:

• Customer Management
• Multiple Delivery Sites
• Multiple Contact Persons
• GST Billing
• Invoice Management
• Inventory Management
• Fuel Purchase
• Payment Tracking
• Reports
• Dashboard

Future modules include:

• Vehicle Management
• Driver Management
• Fuel Dispatch
• Fuel Delivery
• Purchase Orders
• Delivery Challans
• Government API Integration (e-Invoice / e-Way Bill)
• Multi-user Authentication
• RBAC
• Audit Logs
• Notifications
• Multi Branch
• Multi Company (SaaS)

The architecture must support all of these.

